Hungary's Kata Blanka Vas after they had threatened to contest gold between them by opening a half-a-minute lead.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999922160896, \"rank\": 6.533928992473839e-09, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8970879079552332, \"rank\": 0.1147177051083526, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9998813827159748, \"rank\": 0.00011832483199146495, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999866570764205, \"rank\": 1.2204301470036108e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The decisive moment\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 313}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 325}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 468}, {\"ngram\": \"a half-a-minute lead\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kopecky and Faulkner got within touching distance on the final leg-sapping ascent of Montmartre and hung on during a nerve-shredding descent through the narrow, twisty cobbled streets from the highest point in Paris and down to the finish line in the shadow of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999922160896, \"rank\": 6.533928992473839e-09, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 0.9999999998265139, \"rank\": 1.734321633662359e-10, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.20865905118847e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"touching distance\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"the final leg-sapping ascent\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"a nerve-shredding descent\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"the narrow, twisty cobbled streets\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 699}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest point\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadow\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew Kopecky wanted to catch the front two, so I knew she'd ride with me,\\\" explained Faulkner.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999922160896, \"rank\": 6.533928992473839e-09, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then instead of taking a moment to pause for breath ahead of a likely sprint, Faulkner went for glory, immediately opening up a gap as her rivals looked at each other, and by the time they reacted, she had gone.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999922160896, \"rank\": 6.533928992473839e-09, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"breath\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"a likely sprint\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 996}, {\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"her rivals\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1078}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking after the race, the American, who is also her country's road race champion, explained she felt she had no option of beating Vos and Kopecky in a sprint.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999933981402691, \"rank\": 4.155900601425371e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"her country's road race champion\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"no option\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When we were gaining, I knew I had to go solo to the finish.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew I could not beat Lotte or Vos on the line.\\\"\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lotte\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew I had to attack them as soon as we caught them.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew they were sprinters,\\\" she explained, adding that the fact Vos is Dutch, Kopecky from Belgium and Vas, Hungarian would work in her favor.\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1513, \"end\": 1518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.579970733516765, \"rank\": 0.7002163787443253, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8970879079552332, \"rank\": 0.1147177051083526, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.7309895010041052, \"rank\": 0.3679829776293731, \"text\": \"Hungarian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sprinters\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"Vas\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"her favor\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew they did not want to work together - they were three different countries.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1667, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three different countries\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew if I got a small gap they would have to race for second,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a small gap\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1695}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She put her head down and went for glory, without looking back.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1807, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her head\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just counted to 10 about 10 times until I hit the finish line,\\\" commented the rider.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, Faulkner was so focused on the line, that despite winning by 58 seconds as the three behind focused on a sprint for the remaining medals, she kept her head down and did not stop pedaling until well over the finish, meaning there was no repeat of Remco Evenepoel's iconic celebration after winning Saturday's men's race.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999922160896, \"rank\": 6.533928992473839e-09, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"58 seconds\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"the remaining medals\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \"her head\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"no repeat\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday's men's race\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was pretty sure I'd won but it was like 'what in the world just happened?'\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I could not process it.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took me a few minutes.\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to double and triple check that I won gold.\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew it but I did not know it,\\\" admitted a jubilant Faulkner.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": [{\"begi